# Discord Chat Analysis

## 1. Summary
The chat segment discusses issues with a plugin for an AI agent named Eliza. User lantianlaoli is experiencing problems with action recognition in their custom plugin called "quokkaStep" that builds on Raydium. The plugin is supposed to recognize specific actions like "GENERATE_RAYDIUM_CLMM_CONFIG" but is instead defaulting to a "CONTINUE" action. The user notes that the plugin worked with OpenRouter but is having issues after switching to the Gemini model. Shaw mentions that the project has an autodoc package that generates documentation automatically in CI, with some hand-written docs and AI-generated content to fill gaps.

## 2. FAQ
Q: Is the document still work? (asked by lantianlaoli) A: Unanswered
Q: Why is the agent not judging text as the action and triggering but continuing instead? (asked by lantianlaoli) A: Unanswered

## 3. Help Interactions
Helper: Kenk | Helpee: lantianlaoli | Context: User having issues with Eliza agent configuration | Resolution: Directed user to www.eliza.how for assistance

## 4. Action Items
Technical: Investigate why custom action "GENERATE_RAYDIUM_CLMM_CONFIG" is being interpreted as "CONTINUE" after switching from OpenRouter to Gemini | Mentioned By: lantianlaoli
Documentation: Check autodoc package for documentation generation | Mentioned By: shaw
